RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WEST BAY raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the turn, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear in the lane. WATER TO WINE pressed the pace between horses up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the turn and could not go with the winner in the stretch but kept on to the finish. BURN BOSS led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the bend and was caught entering the stretch but chased the winner home from there. HE'S CONNECTED raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter, came around the turn in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. NOT A DANCE stalked the pacesetter between horses up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and faded in the stretch. FALCONITE stumbled leaving the gate, recovered to track the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the four path and tired in the lane. FINBARFUREY pulled up shortly after leaving the gate and was vanned off after walking onto the van. NORTHERN COCKTAIL hopped up leaving the gate, pulled up in the opening furlong and was vanned off after walking onto the van.

ENTRY.NAME: Not a Dance
ENTRY.OWNER: Wolff Robert E and Wolff Perry

ENTRY.NAME: Northern Cocktail
ENTRY.OWNER: Woolley, Jr. Bennie L. and Mitchek, Sam

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Turf CR: 99. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 14 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Claiming Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $40,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it willb e run at a distance of 1 Mile and 1/16 on the main track.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GYPSY WIFE saved ground around the first turn, led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way while racing in the two path around the bend and dueled gamely to the wire to hold the win. INTENSE COMPANY (IRE) saved ground early, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far turn and dueled in the lane but could not go by the winner. LATIN NIKKITA raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path, began a bid while switching inside in upper stretch and gained ground late. FALL MOON raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the three path and finished evenly while never threatening. HURRICAIN HUNTER raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn still in the two path and made no bid. TOM'S GIRL saved ground around the first turn, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and faded from there.

ENTRY.NAME: Intense Company (IRE)
ENTRY.OWNER: Leroy and Linda Arnoldi Leroy and Arnoldi Linda

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota Bred Claimi ng Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FURY KAP raced in the two path around the first turn, led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way while racing in the two path around the far turn and held clear in the stretch. GHOST STALKER saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. MAKE NOISE trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the three path and improved position in the lane. LAST MARTINI tracked the pace setter from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the two path and kept on to the wire but was outfinished late. JOKER MATT raced in the three path early, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and chased on to the wire but was outkicked late.
